The paper focuses on interpreting Visual Question Answering (VQA) models, which involves analyzing both images and text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image analysis and understanding. The paper also involves natural language processing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with deep neural networks, which are a common tool in many AI research fields, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and interpreting the output of the VQA model, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
